<div class="mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id="Lomachenko_vs._Lpez"><span id="Lomachenko_vs._L.C3.B3pez"></span>Lomachenko vs. Lpez</h4><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: Lomachenko vs. Lpez"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1320445320" /><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Vasiliy_Lomachenko_vs._Te%C3%B3fimo_L%C3%B3pez" title="Vasiliy Lomachenko vs. Tefimo Lpez">Vasiliy Lomachenko vs. Tefimo Lpez</a></div>
<p>In September 2020, Lomachenko agreed to fight newly crowned undefeated IBF lightweight champion, <a href="/wiki/Te%C3%B3fimo_L%C3%B3pez" class="mw-redirect" title="Tefimo Lpez">Tefimo Lpez</a>, on 17 October 2020 at the MGM Grand Conference Center in <a href="/wiki/Paradise,_Nevada" title="Paradise, Nevada">Paradise, Nevada</a>. With no live audience due to the <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic" title="COVID-19 pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a>, Lomachenko suffered the second defeat of his career, losing by UD with the scorecards reading 116112, 117111, and 119109.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-137" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-137"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>137<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Judge Julie Lederman's scorecard of 119109, was criticized for giving Lomachenko only a single round.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-138" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-138"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>138<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-139" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-139"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>139<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-140" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-140"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>140<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> The first seven rounds saw Lpez staying behind his jab and going to the body, with Lomachenko offering little in response. In the second half, Lomachenko started coming out more offensively, landing more punches. In the final round, Lpez landed 50 of 98 punches thrown (51%), the most an opponent has landed on Lomachenko in a round. According to CompuBox stats, Lomachenko landed 141 of 321 thrown (44%), while Lpez landed 183 of 659 thrown (28%).<sup id="cite&#95;ref-141" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-141"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>141<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Days after the fight, Lomachenko underwent surgery on his right shoulder.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-142" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-142"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>142<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Lpez declined to give Lomachenko a rematch, explaining that "everybody [in Lomachenko's camp] was being a dick to me, my father. He [Lomachenko] didn't want to put a rematch clause in our contract."<sup id="cite&#95;ref-143" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-143"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>143<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>According to <a href="/wiki/Nielsen_Media_Research" title="Nielsen Media Research">Nielsen Media Research</a>, the fight averaged 2,729,000 viewers and peaked at 2,898,000 viewers. The highest viewership for any boxing in the United States since <a href="/wiki/Manny_Pacquiao_vs._Jeff_Horn" title="Manny Pacquiao vs. Jeff Horn">Manny Pacquiao vs. Jeff Horn</a> in 2017. Bob Arum estimated more than 4 million viewers watched including <a href="/wiki/ESPN_Deportes" title="ESPN Deportes">ESPN Deportes</a> and ESPN+.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-144" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-144"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>144<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-145" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-145"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>145<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id="Lomachenko_vs._Nakatani">Lomachenko vs. Nakatani</h4><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: Lomachenko vs. Nakatani"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1320445320" /><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Vasiliy_Lomachenko_vs._Masayoshi_Nakatani" title="Vasiliy Lomachenko vs. Masayoshi Nakatani">Vasiliy Lomachenko vs. Masayoshi Nakatani</a></div>
<p>Lomachenko made his comeback in a fight against <a href="/wiki/Masayoshi_Nakatani" title="Masayoshi Nakatani">Masayoshi Nakatani</a> on 26 June 2021.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-146" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-146"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>146<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Lomachenko and Nakatani both shared a common loss to undefeated unified lightweight champion <a href="/wiki/Te%C3%B3fimo_L%C3%B3pez" class="mw-redirect" title="Tefimo Lpez">Tefimo Lpez</a>, which Lomachenko cited as the reason why he chose Nakatani as his next opponent, saying, "I want to compare myself with this guy, he was close with [Lpez] in their fight."<sup id="cite&#95;ref-147" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-147"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>147<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Nakatani had a 6-inch height and reach advantage over Lomachenko.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-148" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-148"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>148<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> The fight against Nakatani was only the second fight of Lomachenko's career in which a world title was not at stake, after his professional debut against Jos Luis Ramrez in 2013.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-149" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-149"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>149<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> On the night, Lomachenko scored a knockdown in the fifth round en route to a ninth-round technical knockout victory. After the fight, he made clear his intentions of wanting to rematch Lpez in the winter, saying, "December, January, February. I'm waiting."<sup id="cite&#95;ref-150" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-150"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>150<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id="Lomachenko_vs._Commey">Lomachenko vs. Commey</h4><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=29" title="Edit section: Lomachenko vs. Commey"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1320445320" /><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Vasiliy_Lomachenko_vs._Richard_Commey" title="Vasiliy Lomachenko vs. Richard Commey">Vasiliy Lomachenko vs. Richard Commey</a></div>
<p>In an attempt to put his name back into contention for a shot at his old titles, Lomachenko agreed to face former IBF lightweight champion, <a href="/wiki/Richard_Commey" title="Richard Commey">Richard Commey</a>, on 11 December 2021 in New York. On fight night Lomachenko was listed as a 10-1 favorite.
</p><p>Lomachenko dropped Commey in the seventh round courtesy of a left hook, later pleading with the corner of the still unsteady Commey to stop the fight. They refused, and Commey survived and went the full 12 rounds. The judges scored it 119108, 119108, and 117110, all for Lomachenko. When asked about fighting newly crowned unified lightweight champion, <a href="/wiki/George_Kambosos_Jr." title="George Kambosos Jr.">George Kambosos Jr.</a>, who had upset Teofimo Lpez a few weeks previously, Lomachenko jumped at the idea, stating that he 'needs this chance' and would be willing to fly to Australia if necessary.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-151" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-151"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>151<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id="Cancelled_Kambosos_fight">Cancelled Kambosos fight</h4><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=30" title="Edit section: Cancelled Kambosos fight"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In December 2021, <a href="/wiki/Top_Rank" title="Top Rank">Top Rank</a> president, Todd DuBoef stated Lomachenko would fight in the first half of 2022, with a fight against newly crowned unified lightweight champion Kambosos on the cards. Kambosos was now insistent that he make his first world title defence in Australia, preferably a stadium, having been on the road for his last seven fights, going back to 2017. Lomachenko was Arum's first choice to land the fight.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-152" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-152"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>152<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-153" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-153"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>153<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Eddie Hearn, promoter of WBC champion <a href="/wiki/Devin_Haney" title="Devin Haney">Devin Haney</a>, was also trying to secure the fight for his boxer against Kambosos. Arum felt Lomachenko would make more commercial sense, as Haney was not well known, due to limited exposure.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-154" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-154"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>154<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> On 15 February 2022, ESPN reported that Kambosos would fight on 5 June at <a href="/wiki/Docklands_Stadium" title="Docklands Stadium">Marvel Stadium</a> in Melbourne, Australia, with Lomachenko as the frontrunner. Lomachenko had agreed his side of the deal, which included a rematch clause for a return bout in Australia if Lomachenko was successful.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-155" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-155"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>155<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>On 24 February, plans changed when <a href="/wiki/Russian_invasion_of_Ukraine" title="Russian invasion of Ukraine">Russia launched an invasion of Ukraine</a>, which saw Lomachenko return to his home country to aid in the war effort. Arum was hopeful the fight with Kambosos could still take place in the fall.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-156" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-156"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>156<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-157" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-157"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>157<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-158" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-158"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>158<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> On 20 March, Lomachenko was given permission to leave Ukraine in order to face Kambosos in Australia. However, he declined, opting to stay and fight for his country.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-159" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-159"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>159<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-160" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-160"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>160<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> This allowed Haney to travel to Australia and challenge Kambosos. DuBoef told Sky Sports that Lomachenko would need to make a decision after their fight, as all parties agreed he should fight the winner.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-161" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-161"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>161<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> In June, Kambosos lost his titles to WBC champion <a href="/wiki/Devin_Haney" title="Devin Haney">Devin Haney</a>, who thereby became the <a href="/wiki/Undisputed_championship_(boxing)" title="Undisputed championship (boxing)">undisputed</a> lightweight champion.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-162" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-162"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>162<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id="Lomachenko_vs._Ortiz">Lomachenko vs. Ortiz</h4><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=31" title="Edit section: Lomachenko vs. Ortiz"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>On 7 July 2022, Top Rank president, Todd DuBoef, indicated Lomachenko was planning a return to the boxing ring in October.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-163" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-163"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>163<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> On 17 August, Lomachenko agreed to fight former sparring partner, 26 year old <a href="/wiki/Jamaine_Ortiz" title="Jamaine Ortiz">Jamaine Ortiz</a> (1601, 8 KOs), headlining a Top Rank ESPN card. The fight was a huge step up in competition for Ortiz, who burst onto the scene following his win over former world champion <a href="/wiki/Jamel_Herring" title="Jamel Herring">Jamel Herring</a> in May.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-164" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-164"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>164<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-165" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-165"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>165<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> A week later it was confirmed the fight would take place on 29 October 2022, Lomachenko's first fight in 10 months, at the <a href="/wiki/The_Theater_at_Madison_Square_Garden" title="The Theater at Madison Square Garden">Hulu Theatre at Madison Square Garden</a> in New York.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-166" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-166"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>166<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Arum praised Lomachenko and said of the fight, Vasiliy Lomachenko is a credit to his country and the sport of boxing. When his country needed him, Vasiliy did not hesitate. We are thrilled that he is safe and fighting once again at Hulu Theater at Madison Square Garden, his home away from home. Jamaine Ortiz is a young, hungry, undefeated fighter who understands that a victory over a living legend like Loma would be life-changing. A win here for Lomachenko would move him closer to challenging the winner of the <a href="/wiki/Devin_Haney_vs._George_Kambosos_Jr_II" title="Devin Haney vs. George Kambosos Jr II">Haney vs. Kambosos rematch</a>.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-167" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-167"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>167<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-168" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-168"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>168<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Lomachenko weighed 134.6 pounds, while Ortiz, who was jeered weighed 134 pounds.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-169" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-169"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>169<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>After a very competitive 12 round battle, in front of 4,586 in the arena, Lomachenko emerged victorious with a unanimous decision, the three judges scoring the fight 115113, 116112, and 117111.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-170" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-170"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>170<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Despite the pressure from Lomachenko in the opening round, Ortiz's counter punching caused a red mark under his right eye. The injury worsened in the second round after a clash of heads. Ortiz's eye began to swell after Lomachenko picked up the pace in the fifth round, landing combinations. In the ninth, Lomachenko forced Ortiz to hold after badly wobbling him, only for Ortiz to come back strong in the final minute. Lomachenko did the better work in the championship rounds, showing his experience. Ortiz had only previously been the 10-round distance prior to this bout. Ortiz believed he won the fight. In the post-fight, he said, "I thought I won the fight. Decision is what it is. I thought this was gonna be my night." Lomachenko stated he wanted to be more active going forward. He also praised Ortiz for his efforts.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-171" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-171"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>171<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-172" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-172"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>172<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-173" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-173"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>173<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Lomachenko was credited with landed 125 of 571 punches thrown (22%) and Ortiz landed 122 of 607 thrown (20%). Ortiz out-landed Lomachenko 1074-92 in power shots landed.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-174" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-174"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>174<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-175" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-175"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>175<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id="Lomachenko_vs._Haney">Lomachenko vs. Haney</h4><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=32" title="Edit section: Lomachenko vs. Haney"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1320445320" /><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Devin_Haney_vs_Vasiliy_Lomachenko" class="mw-redirect" title="Devin Haney vs Vasiliy Lomachenko">Devin Haney vs Vasiliy Lomachenko</a></div>
<p>On 29 March 2023, it was confirmed that Lomachenko would take on undisputed lightweight champion <a href="/wiki/Devin_Haney" title="Devin Haney">Devin Haney</a> on 20 May 2023 at the MGM Grand Garden Arena, Paradise, Nevada, U.S.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-176" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-176"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>176<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> With Lomachenko coming in as the underdog for the first time in his career, much of the bout turned out to be closely contested, with both men finding success, Lomachenko scoring with clean combinations to the head, while Haney countered consistently with solid body shots. Late in the fight, Lomachenko became increasingly dominant, finding particular success in the 10th and 11th rounds. However, Haney rallied to win the final round on all three judges' scorecards.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-:0&#95;177-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:0-177"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>177<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-:2&#95;178-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:2-178"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>178<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-:3&#95;179-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:3-179"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>179<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-:4&#95;180-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:4-180"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>180<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Ultimately, Lomachenko suffered his third professional defeat, losing via unanimous decision with scores of 116112, 115113 and 115113, all in favor of the champion Haney who retained his world titles.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-181" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-181"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>181<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> However, the decision was greatly disputed, as many onlookers felt Lomachenko had done enough to win, including fellow boxers <a href="/wiki/Shakur_Stevenson" title="Shakur Stevenson">Shakur Stevenson</a> and <a href="/wiki/Jorge_Linares" title="Jorge Linares">Jorge Linares</a>, who had previously predicted a Haney victory.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-:5&#95;182-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:5-182"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>182<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-:2&#95;178-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:2-178"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>178<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-183" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-183"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>183<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-184" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-184"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>184<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-185" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-185"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>185<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Judge Dave Moretti's scorecard, giving round 10 to Haney despite Lomachenko dominating that round, was heavily criticised.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-:0&#95;177-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:0-177"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>177<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-186" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-186"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>186<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Others argued that as the fight had been close, a narrow result for Haney was not unreasonable.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-:4&#95;180-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:4-180"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>180<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> CompuBox punch stats suggested Lomachenko had landed 124 of 564 punches thrown (22%), while Haney landed 110 of 405 (27%), with both boxers outlanding the other in five rounds each, the other two rounds being even.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-:3&#95;179-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:3-179"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>179<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Lomachenko believed he had won and his team subsequently stated they would file an appeal regarding the result. Haney on his part praised Lomachenko, calling him his toughest opponent yet.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-:5&#95;182-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:5-182"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>182<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-:2&#95;178-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:2-178"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>178<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Regardless of the result, the fight and the performances of both men were widely praised. It was described by multiple accounts as "thrilling", with Lomachenko's display against a substantially younger and larger opponent being highly lauded.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-:2&#95;178-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:2-178"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>178<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-:4&#95;180-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:4-180"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>180<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id="Lomachenko_vs._Kambosos">Lomachenko vs. Kambosos</h4><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=33" title="Edit section: Lomachenko vs. Kambosos"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>On 16 August 2023, Arum squashed rumours that Lomachenko was ducking <a href="/wiki/Shakur_Stevenson" title="Shakur Stevenson">Shakur Stevenson</a>. Stevenson also posted tweets labelling Lomachenko a chicken. Arum stated the Lomachenko declined a fight with Stevenson due to the ongoing Russian-Ukraine conflict. Arum also denied rumours that Lomachenko would fight <a href="/wiki/George_Kambosos_Jr." title="George Kambosos Jr.">George Kambosos Jr.</a> (212, 10 KOs) in Australia. According to Arum, Lomachenko would not discuss any fights for the remainder of 2023.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-187" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-187"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>187<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-188" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-188"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>188<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> In November 2023, Kambobos' promoter <a href="/wiki/Lou_DiBella" title="Lou DiBella">Lou DiBella</a> said a fight between the two would happen in Spring of 2024.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-189" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-189"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>189<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> During an interview on 19 December, Arum said, We're trying to finalize a world title fight at 135 pounds between Lomachenko and Kambosos. I really believe we've made a lot of progress. I believe that fight will happen sometime in April in Australia. I'm looking forward to it. Australia is a great country. The title in question was believed to be the vacant <a href="/wiki/List_of_IBF_world_champions#Lightweight" title="List of IBF world champions">IBF lightweight</a> belt. The belt was made vacant by <a href="/wiki/Devin_Haney" title="Devin Haney">Devin Haney</a>, who decided to move up a weight class.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-190" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-190"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>190<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-191" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-191"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>191<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> A deal was finalised on 14 January 2024 to take place in Australia on 12 May for the vacant IBF title.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-192" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-192"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>192<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-193" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-193"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>193<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-194" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-194"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>194<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> On 31 January, the fight was made official to take place at the <a href="/wiki/Perth_Arena" title="Perth Arena">RAC Arena</a> in <a href="/wiki/Perth" title="Perth">Perth, Australia</a>. The fight would air primetime in the United States on 11 May.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-195" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-195"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>195<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-196" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-196"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>196<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> During a presser, Lomachenko said his goal was to win the IBF title, and then aim for undisputed.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-197" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-197"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>197<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Lomachenko admitted he was at the later stages of his career. He had found it more difficult after recent fights for his body recover. He was always the smaller man in the ring with anyone he fought in the lightweight division.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-198" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-198"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>198<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Lomachenko weighed 134.9 pounds and Kambosos weighed 134.2 pounds.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-199" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-199"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>199<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The fight took place in front of a sold-out crowd of 14,147. In one of his most dominant performances of recent years, Lomachenko won the fight by TKO in the 11th round to become win the vacant IBF world title. With the win, he had now won a world title from all four major organizations. Lomachenko was in control throughout the fight, however Kambosos was credited for not giving up. By round 8, Kambosos had a cut on his right eyelid and in the ninth, he had blood streaming down his face. He dropped Kambosos once with body shots before downing him again soon after with a continued body attack, after which the referee stopped the fight, with Kambosos' corner throwing in the towel at the same time.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-200" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-200"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>200<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-201" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-201"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>201<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-202" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-202"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>202<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>According to CompuBox, Kambosos landed just 40 of his 371 punches (11%), compared to Lomachenko's 175 of 480 (37%). After the fight, Kambosos paid respect, stating, "He's a legend of the sport ... He's one of the best fighters in history." Arum called it a "vintage Loma performance." At the time of stoppage, Lomachenko was ahead 99-91 (twice) and 98-92 on the scorecards. Lomachenko gave no indication on what he wanted to do next in his career, but regaining a world title was a start.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-203" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-203"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>203<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-204" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-204"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>204<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-205" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-205"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>205<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id="Failed_Gervonta_Davis_negotiations">Failed Gervonta Davis negotiations</h4><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=34" title="Edit section: Failed Gervonta Davis negotiations"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Following Lomachenko's victory over Kambosos, discussions for a unification bout against undefeated <a href="/wiki/World_Boxing_Association" title="World Boxing Association">WBA</a> lightweight champion <a href="/wiki/Gervonta_Davis" title="Gervonta Davis">Gervonta Davis</a> commenced, with both sides initially showing interest. However, in July 2024, Lomachenko's manager Egis Klimas announced that talks had been cut short, due to Lomachenko refusing the fight: "Loma is not in the mood right now, he doesn't have the motivation at the moment. He's taking off, he wants to spend more time with the family. He doesn't want to do anything until the end of the year. So he's definitely not coming to the ring until the end of the year."<sup id="cite&#95;ref-206" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-206"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>206<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-207" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-207"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>207<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Retirement">Retirement</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=35" title="Edit section: Retirement"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>After hinting at retirement since the beginning of 2025, Lomachenko officially announced his retirement on June 5 via a video he posted on his social media channels.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-:6&#95;9-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:6-9"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>9<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> In the video, he said:
</p>
<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r1244412712">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 32px}.mw-parser-output .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;margin-top:0}@media(min-width:500px){.mw-parser-output .templatequotecite{padding-left:1.6em}}</style><blockquote class="templatequote"><p>"I'm grateful for every victory and defeat inside the ring and outside the ring. I'm thankful that as my career comes to an end, I've gained clarity about the direction a person must take in order to achieve true victory, not just in the ring.
</p><p>I thank God for my honest and wonderful and kind parents for their care, love and warmth I've felt throughout my life. My father taught me not only boxing, but how to be a role model for my own children.
</p><p>I've made many mistakes in life and in the gym but he was always by my side, correcting me when needed. I have many warm memories.
</p><p>
To my family, you have always stood by me. You shared in my victories and you felt the pain of my losses. Those losses only made us stronger."</p></blockquote>
<p>Lomachenko also paid tribute to his father and trainer. There were multiple tribute posts from boxing media and his peers later that day praising Lomachenko for what he achieved in his career. He finished his professional career with 18 wins from 21 fights. 17 were world title fights.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-208" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-208"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>208<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-209" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-209"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>209<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Personal_life">Personal life</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=36" title="Edit section: Personal life"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Lomachenko is married to Olena, and they have two children.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-210" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-210"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>210<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> As of 2019<sup id="cite&#95;ref-211" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-211"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>211<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> (and since at least 2016),<sup id="cite&#95;ref-212" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-212"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>212<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> he lives in <a href="/wiki/Camarillo,_California" title="Camarillo, California">Camarillo, California</a>, and trains in nearby <a href="/wiki/Oxnard,_California" title="Oxnard, California">Oxnard</a>, just north of Los Angeles.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-213" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-213"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>213<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The face tattooed on Lomachenko's torso is that of his father and trainer, Anatoly Lomachenko.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-214" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-214"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>214<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>During the <a href="/wiki/2022_Russian_invasion_of_Ukraine" title="2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine">2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine</a>, Lomachenko joined the Ukrainian army on paper.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-16184752lomachenko&#95;215-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-16184752lomachenko-215"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>215<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Lomachenko was in Greece when the invasion began (on 24 February 2022), and his flight home to Ukraine the next day was delayed due to air traffic being grounded.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-33388013lomachenko&#95;216-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-33388013lomachenko-216"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>216<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> He managed to get into Ukraine by flying to <a href="/wiki/Bucharest" title="Bucharest">Bucharest</a> and travelling through <a href="/wiki/Romania" title="Romania">Romania</a> on 26 February 2022.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-33388013lomachenko&#95;216-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-33388013lomachenko-216"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>216<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> He followed Ukrainian brothers <a href="/wiki/Wladimir_Klitschko" title="Wladimir Klitschko">Wladimir Klitschko</a> and <a href="/wiki/Vitali_Klitschko" title="Vitali Klitschko">Vitali Klitschko</a>, former heavyweight boxing champions, who also announced their pledge to protect the capital of Ukraine, Kyiv, in February 2022.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-217" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-217"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>217<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Upon his return to Ukraine,<sup id="cite&#95;ref-33388013lomachenko&#95;216-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-33388013lomachenko-216"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>216<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Lomachenko joined the <a href="/wiki/Territorial_defence_battalions_(Ukraine)" class="mw-redirect" title="Territorial defence battalions (Ukraine)">territorial defense battalion</a> of his hometown of <a href="/wiki/Bilhorod-Dnistrovskyi" title="Bilhorod-Dnistrovskyi">Bilhorod-Dnistrovskyi</a> on 27 February 2022.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-16184752lomachenko&#95;215-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-16184752lomachenko-215"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>215<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Fighting_style">Fighting style</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=37" title="Edit section: Fighting style"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Lomachenko is known for his exceptional footwork, head movement, speed, ability to <a href="/wiki/Boxing_styles_and_technique#Switch-Hitter" title="Boxing styles and technique">switch stances</a>, and skill at throwing punches at uncanny angles.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-218" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-218"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>218<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> Lomachenko's inspirations include <a href="/wiki/Muhammad_Ali" title="Muhammad Ali">Muhammad Ali</a>,<sup id="cite&#95;ref-219" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-219"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>219<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Mike_Tyson" title="Mike Tyson">Mike Tyson</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Roy_Jones_Jr." title="Roy Jones Jr.">Roy Jones Jr.</a><sup id="cite&#95;ref-220" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-220"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>220<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p>

<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Titles_in_boxing">Titles in boxing</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=39" title="Edit section: Titles in boxing"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class="mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id="Major_world_titles">Major world titles</h3><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Vasiliy_Lomachenko&amp;action=edit&amp;section=40" title="Edit section: Major world titles"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/List_of_WBO_world_champions#Featherweight" title="List of WBO world champions">WBO featherweight champion</a> (126&#160;lbs)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/List_of_WBO_world_champions#Junior_lightweight" title="List of WBO world champions">WBO super featherweight champion</a> (130&#160;lbs)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/List_of_WBA_world_champions#Lightweight" title="List of WBA world champions">WBA (Super) lightweight champion</a> (135&#160;lbs)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/List_of_WBC_world_champions#Lightweight" title="List of WBC world champions">WBC lightweight champion</a> (135&#160;lbs)</li>
